title: Drug intoxication suspected in death of California man at Burning Man festival
description: Leon Reece, who was found unresponsive at the annual Burning Man festival on Friday, is suspected to have died of drug intoxication.

title: Former Proud Boys leader Enrique Tarrio gets 22 years, longest Jan. 6 sentence yet
description: Enrique Tarrio, former Proud Boys chair, will be sentenced Tuesday following his conviction on a seditious conspiracy charge in connection with the Jan. 6 attack on the U.S. Capitol.

title: Joe Jonas files for divorce from Sophie Turner, says marriage is 'irretrievably broken'
description: Singer Joe Jonas filed for divorce from his wife, actor Sophie Turner, on Tuesday, stating that the marriage is "irretrievably broken."

title: Senator appears to suggest bipartisan bill will censor transgender content online
description: A co-sponsor of a bipartisan bill intended to protect children from the dangers of social media and other online content appeared to suggest the measure could be used to steer kids away from seeing transgender content online.

title: NYC TV anchor Ruschell Boone dies of pancreatic cancer at 48
description: Ruschell Boone, an award-winning reporter and anchor for New York City TV station NY1, has died after battling pancreatic cancer over the past year, the station announced Tuesday.

title: Extreme heat forces school closings and early dismissals
description: Extreme heat is causing a rash of school closings and early dismissals this week across the Midwest and northeastern United States, as a late-season heat wave could push temperatures into record-setting territory over the next several days.

title: N.Y. Attorney General Letitia James asks court to sanction Trump, his eldest sons and attorneys
description: New York Attorney General Letitia James is asking the state Supreme Court to sanction former President Donald Trump, his sons Eric and Don Jr., others.

title: United Airlines issued nationwide ground stop due to 'systemwide technology issue'
description: United Airlines briefly requested grounding its fleet nationwide, the airline and Federal Aviation Administration said Tuesday.

title: Mitch McConnell showed 'no evidence' of a seizure disorder or stroke, doctor says
description: "No evidence" that Sen. Mitch McConnell has a seizure disorder or “experienced a stroke" after his freeze-up last week, Capitol physician says in new letter.

title: Alex Murdaugh's defense to seek new trial based on claims of jury tampering
description: WALTERBORO, S.C. — Lawyers for convicted murderer Alex Murdaugh filed a motion Tuesday seeking a new trial after allegedly uncovering evidence of jury tampering.

title: Spanish soccer coach fired in further fallout from unwanted World Cup kiss by sport's president
description: Spain's women's soccer coach was fired on Tuesday just two weeks after leading his team to the World Cup title, the latest fallout from an unwanted celebratory kiss moments after the match.

title: Russia’s ‘General Armageddon’ appears to resurface for the first time since the Wagner mutiny
description: Sergei Surovikin, Russia’s “General Armageddon,”  has been shown in a new photo after going missing in the wake of Prigozhin's Wagner mercenary mutiny.

title: Texas Republicans put Trump ally Attorney General Ken Paxton on trial
description: Texas will have its third-ever impeachment trial, when Attorney General Ken Paxton stands trial on charges of corruption, abuse of public trust and more.

title: Impeachment threats and shutdown fears: Congress returns for a chaotic September
description: Congress returns this week after a month-long summer recess, facing a potential government shutdown and calls to impeach President Joe Biden.

title: ‘Dinner plate-sized’ medical tool found inside woman 18 months after she gave birth
description: A woman suffered crippling pain after a medical device the size of a dinner plate was left inside her abdomen for 18 months after she gave birth via a caesarean section, an official report has said.

title: Kim Jong Un may meet with Putin in Russia for arms talks
description: North Korean leader Kim Jong Un may travel to Russia for talks with President Vladimir Putin over the possible sale of arms to support Moscow’s war in Ukraine, the White House said Monday.

title: Democratic elites struggle to get voters as excited about Biden as they are
description: When party elites look at President Joe Biden, they see the second coming of Franklin D. Roosevelt. When voters view the president, many see an old man.

title: Dodgers pitcher Julio Urías arrested in domestic violence case
description: Dodgers pitcher Julio Urías has been arrested for alleged domestic violence, police said Monday.

title: First lady Jill Biden tests positive for Covid
description: First Lady Jill Biden tested positive for Covid Monday night, the White House said in a statement.
